Arthur<br>
&gt;The passion will follow the people. It always does.&lt;<br><br>
Nice sentiment, but hogwash!  There are a few other threads on this site that include vets and non-vets, but what is happening there?  Many of these sites have been dying a slow death because of waining interest in them.<br><br>
Who are the most passionate groups during the Vietnam war?  My feeling, they were the protestors, secondly, the vets, thirdly, the general population at large.  There is one or two other sites that invites the protestors, but what has become of those sites?  Why do you think that this thread is the only one to break 100 posts much less 150?  No other site has come close to the 100 mark.  Some of those that have been the most passionate and vocal, here on this thread have left no footprint anywhere else.<br><br>
Granted, at times, there are days where there is no activity here.  But does that last long?  Numbers, in themselves, do not make this thread, but the content.  I can safely say that there are very few postings on this thread that I have not derived something from.<br><br>
So, nice thought, but................................
